{
  "texts": [
    "This analysis reveals that, for G-PCC, the subjects are more inclined to choose P2 over P1 and P3.",
    "Given that P1 employs the parameters suggested by the CTC, this study suggests that there are configurations that may result in better subjective performance than the CTC at equal or lower bitrates.",
    "Both P2 and P3 assign higher importance to color than P1 for most rates, with P2 being closer to the CTC and P3 having lower qp values.",
    "It is important to note that neither of the alternative rate allocation strategies was the result of a systematic optimization of the performance according to objective quality measures.",
    "P2 and P3 were defined as means to explore whether different configurations could provide better subjective quality without the goal of maximizing it."
  ]
}